<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="474" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[160,1156,610,704]" box="[160,276,610,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[160,1156,610,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">
Distinguished from known congeners by distinctive filiform E (
<figureCitation box="[879,975,645,669]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b)), C (ovoid, curved tip, 
<figureCitation box="[290,385,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a, b)), presence of a filiform MA and oval, curved RTA (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1113,680,704]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1202,1225]" captionTargetBox="[177,1151,142,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-95@7.[163,1152,142,1171]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Epidius coloratus sp. nov. RMNH 15921. (a) Male palp, ventral view. (b) Same, retrolateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184391/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="474">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(a)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[160,757,749,808]" pageId="6" pageNumber="474" type="etymology">
